{"id":6612,"date":"2018-04-07T16:05:46","date_gmt":"2018-04-07T15:05:46","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/saltinourhair.com\/?p=6612"},"modified":"2021-10-25T13:50:57","modified_gmt":"2021-10-25T12:50:57","slug":"diyaluma-falls-sri-lanka","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/sri-lanka\/diyaluma-falls-sri-lanka\/","title":{"rendered":"Diyaluma Falls: The Second Highest Waterfall in Sri Lanka"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2>Visiting the Diyaluma Falls<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Visiting the waterfall is one of the <a rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https:\/\/saltinourhair.com\/sri-lanka\/ella-sri-lanka\/\" target=\"_blank\">best things to do in Ella<\/a>. The foot of the Diyaluma falls is quite easy to reach within an hour by tuk-tuk, car, or motorbike. The last 15 minutes of the drive will be uphill and the road isn&#x2019;t the best from that point. At the foot of the waterfall: pass the bridge and follow the path to the waterfall.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-3 is-cropped\"><ul class=\"blocks-gallery-grid\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/04\/23155555\/sri-lanka-waterfall.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/noscript><img width=\"270\" height=\"338\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"6617\" class=\"wp-image-6617 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1536px) 100vw, 1536px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/04\/23155555\/sri-lanka-waterfall.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/04\/23155555\/sri-lanka-waterfall-300x375.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/04\/23155555\/sri-lanka-waterfall-600x750.jpg 600w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/04\/23155555\/sri-lanka-waterfall-480x600